Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.92,0:02:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,3:00 a.m. on December 8th, 1941.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.55,0:02:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Simultaneously with the outbreak of the Pacific war, {/At the same time as the news had arrived of }
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.43,0:02:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a coded cable arrived, \Nannouncing the successful landing on the Malay Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The addressee was Lieutenant-General Sakai, \Ncommander of the 23rd Japanese Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.06,0:02:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,At once he sent his men, \Noff to the border of the Kowloon Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.47,0:02:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To his forces, numbering about 30,000 troops, \Nhe ordered the start of the Hong Kong offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.63,0:02:45.65,Sign,,0,0,190,,{\blur0.8\c&HE4E9E1&\bord0\xshad6\yshad3\4c&H656363&\b1\4a&H28&}Episode 6 \N {\fs130} The Fall of Hong Kong
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.17,0:03:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In preparation for the seizure of Hong Kong, \Nthe Japanese army had had gathered intelligence,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.24,0:03:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,creating detailed plans \Nand making timely arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.49,0:03:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy had prepared a line of fortifications \Non Kowloon Peninsula{ in order to stop us}:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.62,0:03:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,from Shau Kei Wan to Golden Hill{金山 - literally "golden mine", maybe replace with kinzan}, \Nto {Upper }Shing Mun Reservoir. {HA also adds here "to Lion Rock." for w/e reason, I don't hear it but maybee it's in the next line}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.98,0:03:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,On this mountain ridge, to the south of the recess, \Nis the heavily fortified position, dubbed "Gin Drinkers Line." {honestly, no clue what's this shinzan, may be "recess in the mountains" but HA's is being constant about translating it as "lion rock" but it'd make no sense, as irl lion rock is to the south of gin drinkers and lit of this is "connecting to the south of this shinzan"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.48,0:03:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Gin Drinkers Line, so peculiarly named after the soldiers' \Ntendency towards too much Gin, {actually he just explains in japanese who "gin drinker" is so I'm having to make shit up here}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.20,0:03:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is a well thought through \Nline of defensive fortifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.01,0:03:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy commander, Major General Maltby, \Nanticipating the outbreak of the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.01,0:03:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,bolstered the Gin Drinkers Line yesterday \Nwith the fresh British 2nd Royal Scots Battalion. {Most of 1941 passed without active duty for the regiment, and with growing concerns about the stability of the Far East, the 2nd Battalion, still based at Hong Kong, moved into defensive positions around the colony. On 8 December, the Battle of Hong Kong began a few hours after the attack on Pearl Harbor; after bitter fighting, the garrison surrendered on Christmas Day. The newly formed 12th Battalion was disbanded and reformed as the 2nd Battalion in May 1942.[53]}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.25,0:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the 2nd and 14th Punjab Battalions from India,  {The 5/7th Battalion, Rajput Regiment[30] took up garrison at Hong Kong in June 1937 followed by the 2/14th Battalion, Punjab Regiment in November 1940.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.00,0:03:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with the 5th and 7th Rajput battalions, were redeployed as well. {, it seems ... arrangement (of resources); deployment; stationing; posting; disposition; configuration; layout}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.55,0:03:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears, the odds are decisively stacked on our side. {superiority; superior power; predominance; preponderance​}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.82,0:03:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us fight the enemy fair and square \Nwith time-proven tactics. {I hope he means this by "successful way"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How many days will it take for the 1st artillery regiment to arrive in a position where they can shell the enemy? {gaining total control (of people or counties); suppression; oppression; control; mastery; ascendancy; supremacy} {it's "reach" in HA's ver for w/e reason}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.52,0:03:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll probably take care of it in a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.77,0:03:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You think they'll make it under a week?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.69,0:03:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.67,0:03:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.11,0:04:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Set the deadline for breaking through \Nthe Gin Drinkers Line to one week! {it was "The preparation period for breaking through the Gin Drinkers Line is one week." in HA's ver but that doesn't make sense: they won't decide on a date to start Pacific war based on the hong kong capture date, so it has to be something like "after a week's bombardment, we'll begin the general offensive" which is a bit closer to what happened irl, but still makes little sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.84,0:04:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll center the shelling \Non a mountain pass next to Golden Hill. {this shinzan again, HA has it "Lion rock" again. He might just be right, but he is still not pointing at where the Lion rock is located irl and it's not even marked on their map so might as well be "mountain recess" as I assumed, but that'd make sense here as lit is "midway between shinzan and Golden hill"; amazingly, if I go the dumb way and write shinzan on-yomi as 新山 that would be the chinese name for Johor Bahru, with which I thought I was done in ep5; I deadass checked every on-yomi reading for every mountain in hong kong and I've still no clue what's shinzan - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_mountains,_peaks_and_hills_in_Hong_Kong}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.29,0:04:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I would ask the artillery detachments \Nto target the middle of this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.48,0:04:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hammer them at full might with our 24 cm howitzers.{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Type_96_24_cm_howitzer}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If we break through in just one place, the rest of the line \Nwould be exposed in the flanks and rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.84,0:04:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, deploy the division's main force \Nto the east and west of Tai Mo Shan. {believing HA, might replace with "the province's highest peak in the golden mountain area" or smt like that since nobody knows this one}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.51,0:04:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All at once, \Nthey'll topple the Gin Drinkers Line. {no clue what's the first word, ki (tree/mood) wo mite? kyu (moment) wo mite?; lit: at kyumitei, all at once, they'll break through ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the same tactics we used \Nin the Russo-Japanese War to seize Port Arthur. {no clue what's that senkun, believing HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.27,0:04:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hong Kong is made up of two administrative subdivisions:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.04,0:04:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the Kowloon Peninsula, bordering \Nthe Chinese mainland, and Hong Kong Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.40,0:04:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Facing them are the forces under Major General Maltby:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.94,0:04:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,from Britain, India, and Canada \Ntwo battalions each, numbering a total of about 12,000 men. {I hope he means this by "centered on two battalions"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.01,0:05:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The meticulous preparation paid off, \Nas when the Japanese finally applied the attack plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.41,0:05:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they met no resistance whatsoever \Nfrom the British defenders. {I hope he means this by "were immediately hit everywhere"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.28,0:05:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the British Army as well
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.66,0:05:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,still had an ace up their sleeve, \Nwhich is the defensive Gin Drinkers Line. {/was expexting to defend on ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.38,0:05:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Only having thoroughly flattened the British positions with unrelenting shelling, ordering the infantry to advance -
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.06,0:05:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,such was the operational plan \Nthe Japanese came up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.84,0:05:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,With that prospect in mind, \Nthe front line battalion commander
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.61,0:05:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,sent out a subordinate, the First Lieutenant, \Non a reconnaissance mission, {this shokosekko again, still no clue what's shoko, but sekko is again certainly "reconnoitering party; scout (army)"; also no clue what's ichi, it's literally "one/1" but I don't think that's how "first Lieutenant works in japanese" and as a name ichi can be only feminine} {HA has it here "Lieutenant Toichi Wakabayashi" somehow but I clearly can't hear him mentioned directly yet, and this is what I could\Nfind about him: During the war, Wakabayashi went into Hong Kong with his regiment, which arrived at the front later than other units. On 9 December, his regimental commander reconnoitered the Needle Hill area and found Shing Mun Redoubt lightly guarded. He was entrusted to conduct additional reconnaissance later that day and had the same conclusion. His commander decided to send a battalion to launch a night attack against the position, and Wakabayashi’s company participated in the attack. He and his men rushed to the top of the Redoubt and he left a marking at the entrance of “Shaftesbury Avenue,” one of the tunnels of the Redoubt. As the action was not approved by the higher command, he was somehow blamed by his regimental commander for taking the position without order, and was forbidden to play an active role throughout the battle. His battalion was sent as the final reserve of the division and was not sent to the Island until 24 December. This possibly explained his survival. - so apparently it's really him who's being sent, but the name is not said explicitly, apparently...?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.06,0:05:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in charge of the forward unit. {no clue what's ikko, also not sure what's hiki here so believing HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.20,0:05:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They were tasked with probing \Nthe British positions in the highlands. {to investigate; to probe into; to spy on; to sound out}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.37,0:06:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant, there it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.96,0:06:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Artillery observation post.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.88,0:06:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.38,0:06:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,let's get a closer look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.33,0:06:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.90,0:06:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Under a moonlight that bright, \Nthe enemy will see you immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, the heavens are on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.19,0:06:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This lieutenant was an officer who had risen from the ranks. {lit: working one's way up commissioned officer}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.24,0:06:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,His battle experience \Nmade that possible in due time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.90,0:07:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's manning it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.48,0:07:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What could be the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.28,0:07:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Breaking through the Gin Drinkers Line starts \Nwith this observation post's wipeout.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.74,0:07:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's something we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.51,0:07:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant, are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We've the element of surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go. It's reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.55,0:07:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There are only 21 of us here. Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"Besides" what? Spit it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.50,0:07:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You were tasked with a reconnaissance mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is insubordination. {HA: This is an act of disobedience.} {he seems indeed to be Toichi Wakabayashi, remember wiki info I found on him before?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.71,0:07:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop it{/don't worry}. We're just doing a bit of mole extermination. {this is literal, not sure why he'd choose moles, maybe because they dig themselves into the ground}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.15,0:07:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Only he, who remains at all times composed \Nis good at decision making. {I really hope he says "the most brilliant display of your heroism is having a sound judgement with a completely cool head" tho not sure about any part of it; HA had it "On the battlefield, there are many things that require arbitrary judgment" and in quotes for w/e reason so I figured it might be some sun tzu quote but no, I can't find a source of it or a general named sukobu ooshi, but HA's ver sounds also very believeable, maybe even more so than mine, no clue what's ooshi in the end}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.16,0:07:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You enter the battle prepared for anything. {adapting oneself to the requirements of the moment; playing by ear; ad hoc approach}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.23,0:07:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You take decisions without hesitating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.19,0:07:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortune smiles to the daring ones, \Nso I don't think you are to blame. {lit is "i don't think the action of judgment is (not) always; (not) necessarily; (not) entirely; (not) all goes against the military rules" - really sounds like he ends the sentence after "(not) always; (not) necessarily; (not) entirely; (not) all" so I'm generally unsure}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.10,0:07:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you'd understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.46,0:07:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you join me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.69,0:07:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.76,0:07:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll make short work of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.11,0:07:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The shortest work, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather! {/get together}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.53,0:08:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I jump in first, \Nthen you jump after and follow my footsteps. {no clue what he means by "uniformly; evenly; equally; indiscriminately; across the board", but with next line in mind, HA's "in line" makes sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.08,0:08:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody outside our line is an enemy! {lit: think that everything that moves to the left and right is enemy}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.06,0:08:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.79,0:09:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{add w/e here, I don't hear anything}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.93,0:09:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{same}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.32,0:09:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the Japanese troop count? {lit: japanese numbers are?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.91,0:09:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably 200-300, up to 400-500.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.35,0:09:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Our garrison is 100 men at best. \NAsk the battalion commander for reinforcements at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.66,0:09:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Use the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.42,0:09:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.32,0:09:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.66,0:09:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.40,0:09:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep calm. No need to panic. {guess, hantai is reverse; opposite; inverse; contrary but idk what it means, maybe "do the opposite"; HA has it "be calm"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:10:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Battalion commander, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.30,0:10:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We've an emergency! {state of emergency; emergency; crisis}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.66,0:10:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.72,0:10:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.90,0:10:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Our reconnaissance party clashed with the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.72,0:10:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A fierce firefight ensued.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.52,0:10:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed. Things are not going according to plan. {lit; it became a problematic thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.70,0:10:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, they're after the glory of beating others to it. {lit: the fame/glory of solo raid on an enemy's camp (for glory)​ was probably what they aimed at}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.58,0:10:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's done is done. {cannot be helped; unavoidable}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.33,0:10:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Order the 3rd Battalion to attack immediately, \Nwith the 2nd Battalion covering them. {/supporting}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.04,0:10:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.38,0:10:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing so would upset \Nall the army's operational planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.84,0:10:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Scouts are not lambs for slaughter. {lit: we can't letting (someone) die without helping}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.01,0:10:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The division commander was rash to... {no clue what's ichiwo, may be "tentatively; for the time being" but they never mentioned it before; no clue what's kakka either, and not sure which division commander they refer to - most likely the reconnaissance party one; HA's: the intentions of ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.68,0:10:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I take full responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.26,0:10:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.87,0:10:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They've no shred of military discipline!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.02,0:10:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to rebuke them all, \Nas soon as this recon party is back!  {lit: immediately withdraw ... to the unit they belong to and ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.76,0:10:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.42,0:10:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,An army must, at all times, base all its actions \Non the prudent operational plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.54,0:10:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Arbitrary actions are damnable! {/self-willed/selfish/on your own}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.22,0:11:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's get in there. {to plunge into; to charge into; to rush into; to ram into; to crash into}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge! {act. "continue/advance/keep on"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.98,0:11:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander-in-chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.32,0:11:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Reinforcements! Please send in reinforcements!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.06,0:11:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We're six feet under if you don't! {annihilation; total destruction; complete destruction; crushing defeat}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.13,0:12:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Just try and listen to this rumble!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.69,0:12:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible. The Japanese engaged us here as well! \NNo time for a counterattack. Disengage and fall back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.83,0:12:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You order us to fall back, and yet, all the retreat routes \Nare now in Japanese hands! {to get a hold of; to obtain; to seize; to catch; to arrest}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.91,0:12:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why I loath these mole fortifications! {/why I hate}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.79,0:13:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.92,0:13:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Division commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.92,0:13:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Look there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.11,0:13:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They bagged the bastards.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.32,0:13:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ridiculous!
