Dialogue: 1,0:13:27.08,0:13:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want the enemy to reoccupy fortifications \Nwe secured with so much trouble, {lit: thinking there's no need to return to the enemy the position seized with all that trouble}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.87,0:13:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so I asked the front line commander \Nto stay put for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.87,0:13:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At least until this key position \Nis duly secured.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.70,0:13:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If we leave it up to them, we can shove \Nour operational plans to where the sun doesn't shine! {spoiled; spoilt; ruined; wasted (chance, etc.); messed up; destroyed; (coming to) nothing}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.04,0:13:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, in truth, we must give them an earful. \NInsubordination is grave! {extreme; excessive; terrible; intense; severe; serious; tremendous; heavy (damage)} {unsure it's not hanaganashi - unappealing; uninteresting; lacking charm} {funny to hear about discipline from the Japs, who violated nearly every geneva convention rule}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.38,0:13:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they made it possible for our army \Nto capture in a span of one night
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.87,0:13:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what would have taken a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.58,0:13:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, then, do you suppose we're preparing \Nthe battle plans for? For leisure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.05,0:14:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,By dismissing these scraps for glory, \Nour battle order sinks into chaos! {lit: if we allow/forgive such a solo raid on an enemy's camp (for glory), operation/strategy will only be in disorder; chaos; confusion; mayhem}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.69,0:14:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see the silver lining? \NGoing off-script can also pay off. {adapting oneself to the requirements of the moment; playing by ear; ad hoc approach - I tl'd it this way the last time}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.34,0:14:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it took a great deal of weight \Noff my own shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.76,0:14:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.30,0:14:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, at any rate, reprimanding this reconnaissance party \Nshould be our first priority. {deciding first; settling (a matter) first; first priority}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.97,0:14:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Regarding that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.36,0:14:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if we examine our current situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.48,0:14:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they have indeed opened a large gap \Nin the enemy positions on Gin Drinkers Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.14,0:14:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All over the front line, the British troops \Nare reported to be slowly falling back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.26,0:14:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In the wake of this, all the front line commanders \Ninsist that we take advantage of it{/this opportunity}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.88,0:14:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,by immediately resuming our advance, \Nand seizing as much land from the enemy as we can.{unsusre what he means: all at once, capturing advance}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.14,0:14:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.76,0:14:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I commit to it. {/support}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.64,0:14:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall bring forward \Nan emergency change of plans,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.35,0:14:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and launch an all-out attack along the entire front!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's redeploy our entire {British }army to the Hong Kong Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.38,0:15:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Our new ally Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek{ and his allied armies}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.42,0:15:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,promised to attack the Japanese \Nfrom behind on the Kowloon Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.06,0:15:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This option is favorable to a futile defense of peninsula \Nwith more bloody battles. {lit: it's more effective than defending kowloon peninsula with hard fight; close game; struggle; tight contest}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.43,0:16:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:01.22,0:16:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll order all the troops on the Kowloon Peninsula \Nto withdraw to Hong Kong island{added, he doesn't specify what does he mean by HK}.
